# Rav Legacy RAG API — Project Overview

## What this system is

A production-grade RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) API that answers questions about
Rav Soloveitchik's recorded teachings. Transcripts (`.srt` / `.txt`) are chunked, embedded
into a vector store, and retrieved at query time to ground LLM responses with cited sources.

**Full spec**: `specs/current/architecture.md`

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| API framework | FastAPI 1.0.0 (`rag.app.main`) |
| Embeddings | Google Gemini (`gemini-embedding-001`) |
| LLM | Gemini Flash / GPT-5.2 (switchable via `LLM_CONFIGURATION`) |
| Vector store | Pinecone **or** MongoDB Atlas Vector (switchable via `DATABASE_CONFIGURATION`) |
| Auth | Supabase JWT (`app/services/auth.py`) |
| Rate limiting | Upstash Redis (optional — disabled when token absent) |
| Query persistence | Supabase RPC `submit_user_query` |
| Metrics / exceptions logging | MongoDB |

## Module map

| Directory | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `app/api/v1/` | HTTP routers — no business logic |
| `app/services/` | Business logic (embedding, LLM, auth, sync) |
| `app/db/` | Database connections and retrieval |
| `app/schemas/` | Pydantic contracts (requests, responses, enums) |
| `app/models/` | Internal domain models (not exposed directly) |
| `app/core/config.py` | `Settings` / `SharedSettings` — Pydantic settings |
| `app/core/constants/` | Non-secret defaults (env-overridable) |
| `app/exceptions/` | Typed exception hierarchy |
| `scripts/` | Ingestion and sync scripts |
| `smoke_tests/` | End-to-end smoke test runner + spec |
| `specs/` | Human-readable system specs (current state, future states, migrations) |

## Critical invariants

- **Secrets only in `.env`** — never in `app/core/constants/` or committed to source control.
- **Constants are defaults, not config** — every constant must be overridable via its `Settings` field.
- **No business logic in routers** — routers validate input and delegate to `app/services/`.
- **Typed exceptions only** — raise from `app/exceptions/`, never bare `Exception` or `HTTPException` directly in services.
- Start the server from the repo parent directory: `PYTHONPATH=.. uvicorn rag.app.main:app --port 8000`
